 are positive that you won\'t need to move/rotate the TV, then don\'t cinch down the bolts further (though it is already assembled).  Loosen it just enough so that the movement doesn\'t require too much force.  It didn\'t take long to install this tv mount either.  It bolts to the wall using 6 lag screws: one at each corner, and then two at the center just above and below the \"arm.\"  It comes with all of the lag bolts neccessary for installation to a stud.  In my case, there were two corner bolt holes that miss the stud because of the width of the mounting plate, but this kit comes with anchors and screws for this scenario.  Definitely worth the purchase!',5,'Perfect compatibilty with Sony',1319587200,'10 26, 2011'),(474,'A14O9P3DV5EHKO','0972683275','E. Solch',0,1,'I had to use a hacksaw to cut away part of this to hang my 24&#34; LED TV in my bedroom. Other than that, seems to work fine.',3,'A little big for 24&#34; TV\'s',1359331200,'01 28, 2013'),(475,'A27WRC8KIFFTWS','0972683275','E.Sol',0,0,'The price of this was great, it is strong, holds our Tv without a problem, it is made very well, and in the retail store it goes for more than $100.00 and not made as well. I would so say this is a very awsome buy. I do want to mention I have a 42in.TV',5,'awsome',1362700800,'03 8, 2013'),(476,'AVHB9LLVCTEKY','0972683275','Evan Caltrider',0,0,'I have a 42&#34; Hannspree LCD TV. It weighs 42.5 lbs. Most other reviews said they had a TV smaller than this so I was a little skeptical but got it because of the good price and it said it could hold 60 or so lbs. Most of my reservation was because it was the first time I\'ve mounted a TV and worried it would fall within a week. I\'ve had it over a month and its nice to have it be able to swing out, extend, and angle. I like the fact that I can get a bigger TV and still use this mount as its in my living room. It was not too hard to install. I bought a stud finder because I didn\'t have one and most everything else I already had 