ount the TV to the bracket, but overall a Great Value!!',4,'Great product',1381622400,'10 13, 2013'),(890,'A1S8E2JSVXHIPB','0972683275','Nancy',0,0,'We needed something to Extend our tv away from the hot pipe for the winter and this wall mount did the trick. It went up with no a problems. It worked out very well!',5,'Great Wall mount!!',1378857600,'09 11, 2013'),(891,'A2QBJEHKTD7R6O','0972683275','Nathan',0,0,'its a little flimsy and not the easiest to put together, for the price it works.  But for the quality i\'d go with Cheetah.',3,'difficult mount',1377734400,'08 29, 2013'),(892,'A2LVJDTDXIIY84','0972683275','Nathan',1,10,'So you\'re going through all the possible wall mounts for sale, and you after you\'ve noticed that most of them are north of $50, and many are selling for $80, $100, or more, then you start thinking about this unit.The hope is that you\'ll spend something around twenty bucks on a device built in China (I believe), and use it to secure your flat panel television (your sweet baby) to the wall. Your television probably cost you several hundred dollars, so entrusting it to this wall mount is a big leap of faith.I received mine about three weeks ago, and since I\'m not handy, I had my buddy help me. You better be ready to drill, because you\'re going to be mounting it into the wall with multiple screws/brackets. You have to know how to find the stud in your drywall...It took my friend and I about forty-five minutes to install the unit.Included with the wall mount is a tool, some sort of wrench you will need, but it was so poorly constructed that we wore it away so badly in the first few minutes that it no longer turned the included screws.So far, for the last month, the wall mount has held my 32\" television (which falls within the allotted weight) up to the wall. There are two caveats: firstly, I NEVER pull it out, articulate it, turn it... nothing. I don\'t trust the wall mount enough to do anything but leave the television flush against the wall. Secondly, make sure you have a level with you, not just for installation, but pretty much for the life of the wall mount so you can make sure your television is level from time to time, in case you bump it or move it ever so slightly.Well, that\'s all there is to say. Good luck to you.',2,'VideoSecu Wall Mount Review',1291507200,'12 5, 2010'),(893,'A2J13NR5GB8GYO','0972683275','ncCOPPER',0,0,'Purchased this for a small 22 in TV for bedroom. The mount weighs more than the TV ! That\'s not a complaint though. I actually took down the 22 inch set today and mounted a 37in Sharp Aquos. Much heavier set than 22 in, no issues at all. It supports the 37 in just fine. The set probably weighs 35-40 lbs. For the price, $25,it was a great bargain. Installed it myself into wall studs,very secure.',5,'Awesome price and easy install',1353801600,'11 25, 2012'),(894,'A6D7R8LLIC3FO','0972683275','NC_ILM',0,0,'I wasn\'t sure if I had the right tools, but found all I needed was a socket wrench and screw driver. The mount is already assembled and most of the &#34;stuff&#34; in the box are extensions, bolts, and different size screws you may need depending on your TV and size. They cover all bases! Very easy to assemble... It takes longer to screw the bolts into the wall (2 by 4) then it does to assemble the mount.',5,'They make sure you have everything!!',1394841600,'03 15, 2014'),(895,'A3S1BO0SLFC5H','0972683275','NDM',0,0,'We needed a wall mount for a 32&#8221; TV that was going to be in the screened in porch.  This was one of the brands recommended by the guy that was going to install out wall mount.  I can&#8217;t speak to the ease or difficulty of installation but it looks great and we can swivel it if necessary for best viewing angle.  It\'s also pretty sleek so it doesn\'t butt out too much.  It arrived quickly and it didn&#8217;t take the installer long but of course he was a professional.  Looks great!',5,'Great mount',1377043200,'08 21, 2013'),(896,'A3DKC72AYVYT6T','09726832